originalText.text: Great system. Really easy to use if you're a traveller from out of town, all you need is a credit card. Your first 30 minutes is free so you can keep dropping your bike off at different spots & starting a new one to avoid extra time fees

text.text: Citi bike üö≤ is a really cool bike rental concept in NYC. Easy to find and cheap to rent, I suggest taking the bike and going to Central Park. To stop and visit, leave the bike at the stations outside the Park. Then just take it back and continue on your journey. Are your legs okay? Go to Brooklin Bridge, there is also a Citi Bike station where you can ditch your skinny bike and walk across the bridge, but you can also cross it. You can leave the bike at the station, go to the hotel and pick it up if you come back for a ride in the evening.
